##When we get home, I want you all to stay away from me

WMSYGSDR

Function introduction, each line has the earnest person, again the ordinary person also has the extraordinary story. Huazhong University of Science and Technology Press Official non-fiction story platform, the story of the people will meet here.

There is no good news outside, we have two confirmed cases in the city, they are from Wuhan Back! I didn't dare to tell my father any bad news, for fear that it would be too much for him.

”

1

On January 18,2020, the company's annual convention, as it always was, was a day to go to lunch in the cafeteria, watch shows, perform shows, and go home.

At that time, I wanted to buy some New Year goods home, missed the afternoon show. Until now, I am extremely glad, this time, I did not go to the most foot traffic, the most abundant goods supermarket, but to the home just opened the supermarket.

I can still recall talking to several people in the supermarket that day, and how far away I was from them -- as if these images were repeated many times during my isolation. I am afraid, afraid of being caught, can only talk to myself countless times: Nothing, far away, no close contact, the new supermarket, their health card is certainly new.

On the 19th, I was safe, too. I stayed home for a day and didn't go anywhere.

That night, my classmates called me to ask if I was all right. I also told him, fortunately, the virus infection intensity is low, the source is in Hankou, far away from me, tomorrow will go home, it is all right.

On the 20th, I chose to Carpool. On the bus, the master did not wear a mask, the back row is three people from all over the country to Wuhan Annual Meeting, only one wore a mask. She told the other two to wear masks.

A person from Shenzhen said, nothing, the death of the case has a past history, infection is mostly the elderly, do not worry. She took off her mask and the three chatted happily, spitting wildly. I tucked my face into my collar, didn't say a word, and looked at my phone uncontrollably for what seemed like an eternity.

Not many people wear masks in subway stations or on the subway. I continued to Tuck my face into my collar and stood facing the other door. At the Hankou station there was a great crowd of people, with very few wearing masks, and the crowd was like a pool of stagnant water under the moonlight, Shimmering White.

There are few elderly people who wear masks, and some babies are strapped to their chests by their parents, with no protection. The more I looked, the more terrified I became. I wanted to bury my head in my collar and keep only my eyes.

Finally get on the train, the whole car, even before wearing a mask, also took off. I had to face the window, keep facing the window, and cover my head with my clothes. In the meantime, any cough could make me PARESTHESIA, and an aunt behind me kept retching..

On the train, I finally saw the news came out, my heart is more and more heavy, sank to leave the seat, to see the other car courage are no longer; also dare not drink water, afraid to go through the car to the toilet.

My cousin sent me a message saying: Wait for me outside the station, the car is ready.

I didn't know what to tell her, and finally said, okay, we'll talk less later. Wuhan is a bit serious, go home, you all stay away.

She said, it's not that bad. You're fine.

If only it weren't so bad.

2

Back home, I can find the anti-virus cold powder, Lotus qingwen drink, at dawn, went to the pharmacy to buy a mask, and bought several bags of cold powder. Every New Year, I love to catch a cold, but this year I dare not catch a cold.

On the way home from the drugstore, I was reading all kinds of information and I was very nervous. My hometown in this remote small county town, full of people, people crowded, people to people, they do not care about anything else, the Spring Festival means to them a reunion, but this is the most can not do at this time.

Aunt, uncle back new year, I dare not get too close to them, dare not to talk face to face with them, even if talking, I also deliberately distant. They knew something was up in Hubei, but they didn't know it was this bad.

Sister's child is still very small, fell on the ground, I dare not hold, more dare not touch. He was so young and smiling and my sister's baby that I could only watch from a distance.

I dare not eat with them, holding a bowl outside the door to eat. One day, I didn't even eat to keep from them. I even thought, if only I could be locked up now, so they wouldn't get hurt, not one of them, and I couldn't bear it.

But are you sure you're okay? Are you sure there's no close contact? I don't know, and I daren't know.

Wuhan is closed. I went to the village to register, and I reiterated my willingness to cooperate with any inspection. The village liaison officer made a mistake in the rush, and I got mixed up with another young man who had come back from Shenzhen. He went to check it out, and I stayed.

My aunt and uncle drove back for fear of the highway closure. And my sister took the kids away from home. I can't even say, "it's okay. I'm okay. You're okay. ". This incubation period is so long, who knows?

Finally, the village liaison called me and asked me to check it out. What can we check in the country? Do we have any reagents? I asked them to send a man with me. In less than half an hour, she came to my house with a paramedic and took my temperature, which, thankfully, was 100 degrees. They left their thermometers, told me to take them twice in the morning and twice in the evening, and called to tell them.

On the 28th, a propaganda car pulled up in front of my house. Local police, health workers, liaison officers, town party secretaries, village chiefs and others came to lecture me on the requirements of home segregation.

I saw a lot of neighbors, watching from a distance, I heard neighbors call his children said my home to the "police car. ". I also have to answer questions from the Party secretary: Wuhan let five million people go, why did you come back!

I'm an outsider. Shouldn't I exist? Am I the patient? What, five million people are sick? I explained in vain: I go home every year for Chinese New Year. I bought my ticket on December 22..

3

On the 29th, my sister sent me a message on wechat asking if I was sitting on D2259.

I don't understand. Why are you asking me this? D2259, east of Chengdu, Hankou, 10:36,19:38 east of Chengdu, I always take this train home, just in time, do not hurry, to Chengdu can still eat string with my cousin.

For a minute, I couldn't remember whether I had taken this train back to Sichuan.
I can't even remember how to find out which train to take home.

My sister then sent a picture.

I called out, "Daddy! "

Dad asked me what it was about. I stepped back a few steps before I said to him: You do not come over, I sit this train, this car to go home. The signal at home is very bad, the picture has not shown, my hand has been shaking, heart is like being squeezed tightly with the hand..

"looking for a passenger on January 21 in Carriage 7 of D2259, where a passenger has been diagnosed, please contact your local CDC immediately... "

January 21, D2259, car 7... D2259, Car 7, I am car 7, I am also on D2259. January 21st, 21st. I'm the 20th... Thank God.

At this time, I found that my father has been standing still, looking at me, the color is not good than usual, he has been a serious face, because of this matter, the color is even worse.

"It's all right. I'm on the 20, looking for the 21, " I said with a forced smile. After a while, he said, "I told you, your train on the 20th... what a coincidence... "

It's been a long, long time in isolation.

I dare not say a word to anyone, even if it is far away. Actually, no one talks to me anymore. My father and I, our yard became an island. The people on the other side of the island, with all the excitement, as if they were cut off from us, were safe. On the island, my father and I lived on opposite sides of the island, talking loudly through thick walls.

But what can I say? We do not speak, we are like the island in the silence of the beast, stubborn and endure to live. Is He really alive? How long do we have? Animals don't think about that.

I'm more afraid of the bad news that he needs me to tell him. For his body, I was the Great Depression -- a return from Wuhan, and an exposed return from Hankou.

Dad began to watch TV all day in the house. And I used to sit on the roof with a book.

Every day I sit on the roof, hands of the book just two pages, I unconsciously fell into the memories. Every memory can not leave Wuhan before I have contact with WHO, supermarket cashier, Didi Master: After leaving Wuhan, I have contact with WHO, Dad, cousin, aunt, uncle, uncle, aunt, Dad, drugstore salesman..

You really haven't spoken to them face-to-face?

Each time I ended up blaming myself for not stopping my father when he had to cross the market to buy groceries; for not telling my aunt that her cloth mask was useless; for not wearing it in the first place; Why didn't you come back until the 20th?

Why... Should I. . . Come back?

4

The next few days, the weather is not good, rain, wet and cold, the epidemic situation is also more and more serious, I always dry throat, occasionally also headache, the smell of home disinfection water is very heavy, smoked me more uncomfortable!

I was afraid to tell dad. I was afraid he'd worry. And I was afraid he wasn't feeling well enough to tell me. At night, as soon as I hear him cough, I immediately ask, "how about taking your temperature? "

He keeps saying he's got a bad cough. He's fine. I always repeat: "Any discomfort, fatigue, cough, dyspnea, fever, tell me, do not hide it from me! "

He always said I was nosy.

But I'm afraid he's not, because all the information that's going around is that the elderly are vulnerable and vulnerable, and there are cases where the asymptomatic are fine and their families are infected one after another. This situation is the last thing I need right now.

I'd rather have something happen to me than someone close to me.

Until the last day, when I was finally going off medical observation. The day seemed to go by so slowly that after breakfast I took my temperature again. It was not yet nine o'clock, and I took out my book, sat on the roof, and read a few lines, which I repeated a few moments later, each of which I knew, but which I could not read altogether.

I don't know why, but my head hurts. He wanted to take his temperature again, but he hesitated. I picked it up and put it down again and again.

Dad Sat on his little fishing stool and kept watch at the gate. I told him the liaison wouldn't be here till this afternoon. "I'm not waiting for her, " he said. "I'll sit down. It's a fine day! "

At 5:00 p.m. , the sky cleared, and the setting sun filled our small courtyard. The liaison and the hygienist took my dad's and my last temperature. It was normal. Tell me I can go out, but wear a mask!

The two of them left in the setting sun.

I went back to my dad and told him it was safe for now. I'm sure he simply ignored the "temporary" and jumped to "safe" . For the first time in days, he smiled comfortably and asked for his temperature. "Give me the thermometer, " he said

Next thing I know, the incubation period is up to 24 days. After the first 14 days, I was less anxious, sitting on the roof and reading Love in the Time of Cholera, which I didn't finish, and turning to weather alone.

Today, on Day twenty-five of my stay in Wuhan, after a period of cold and wet weather, I was surrounded by bees and butterflies and golden rape flowers all over the slope. I stood in the rape flower field, smelling the sweet flowers sent by the breeze, suddenly remembered that Wuhan side of the Cherry Blossom is afraid to open it?
